BRASILIA: Saudi Arabia's foreign minister Prince Faisal bin Farhan bin Abdullah on Friday opened the new building of the Kingdom’s embassy in Brazil. Prince Faisal toured the new embassy building and was briefed on the work of the departments during a visit on the sidelines of his official trip to Brazil. During the inauguration of the new building, the foreign minister met with the embassy’s employees, extending his thanks and praise to them for the diplomatic work they do to represent the Kingdom, strengthening bilateral relations with the Brazil, and taking care of Saudi nationals living in Brazil. The opening was attended by the Saudi ambassador to Brazil, Ali bin Abdullah Bahitham, and the Director General of the Office of the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Abdul Rahman Al-Daoud.